## Project Overview

This project is a web application that enables Telegram bot account to serve as a chat bot. It monitors Telegram update events and shows messages that are sent to the bot.
It supports the following use-cases:
 - shows a chat of user that sent a message;
 - stores all the data to local-storage to provide basic persistence;
 - allows to set auto-replies on user commands;
 - send broadcast messages to all or specified users;
 - supports multiple bot accounts;
 - fetch user info;
 - supports wildcard %username%, %first-name% in replies;
 - dark/light themes.

It can be used in emergency cases when bot service is not working, but client requests should be handled immediately.
